018/**
019 * DTO for an HTML <a class="doclink" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/grouping-content.html#the-main-element">&lt;main&gt;</a>
020 * element.
021 *
022 * <p>
023 * The main element represents the main content of the body of a document or application. It is
024 * used to identify the primary content of the page, excluding content that is repeated across
025 * multiple pages such as navigation, headers, footers, and sidebars. The main element should
026 * be used only once per page and contains the central topic or functionality of the page. It
027 * is important for accessibility and helps screen readers identify the main content area.
028 *
029 * <h5 class='section'>Examples:</h5>
030 * <p class='bcode w800'>
031 *    // Simple main content
032 *    Main simple = new Main()
033 *       .children(
034 *          new H1().children("Welcome to Our Site"),
035 *          new P().children("This is the main content of our page.")
036 *       );
037 *
038 *    // Main with styling
039 *    Main styled = new Main()
040 *       ._class("main-content")
041 *       .children(
042 *          new H1().children("About Us"),
043 *          new P().children("Learn more about our company and mission.")
044 *       );
045 *
046 *    // Main with complex content
047 *    Main complex = new Main()
048 *       .children(
049 *          new H1().children("Product Catalog"),
050 *          new Section()
051 *             .children(
052 *                new H2().children("Featured Products"),
053 *                new P().children("Check out our latest offerings.")
054 *             ),
055 *          new Section()
056 *             .children(
057 *                new H2().children("Categories"),
058 *                new Ul().children(
059 *                   new Li().children("Electronics"),
060 *                   new Li().children("Clothing"),
061 *                   new Li().children("Books")
062 *                )
063 *             )
064 *       );
065 *
066 *    // Main with ID
067 *    Main withId = new Main()
068 *       .id("page-main")
069 *       .children(
070 *          new H1().children("Main Content"),
071 *          new P().children("This is the main content area.")
072 *       );
073 *
074 *    // Main with styling
075 *    Main styled2 = new Main()
076 *       .style("max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px;")
077 *       .children(
078 *          new H1().children("Centered Content"),
079 *          new P().children("This content is centered and styled.")
080 *       );
081 *
082 *    // Main with multiple sections
083 *    Main multiSection = new Main()
084 *       .children(
085 *          new Section()
086 *             .children(
087 *                new H1().children("Page Title"),
088 *                new P().children("Introduction to the page content.")
089 *             ),
090 *          new Section()
091 *             .children(
092 *                new H2().children("Content Section"),
093 *                new P().children("Detailed content goes here.")
094 *             ),
095 *          new Section()
096 *             .children(
097 *                new H2().children("Conclusion"),
098 *                new P().children("Summary and closing thoughts.")
099 *             )
100 *       );
101 *
102 *    // Main with article
103 *    Main withArticle = new Main()
104 *       .children(
105 *          new Article()
106 *             .children(
107 *                new H1().children("Article Title"),
108 *                new P().children("Article content goes here."),
109 *                new Footer().children("Article footer")
110 *             )
111 *       );
112 * </p>
113 *
114 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
115 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/JuneauBeanHtml5">juneau-bean-html5</a>
116 * </ul>
117 */
118@Bean(typeName="main")
119@FluentSetters
120public class Main extends HtmlElementContainer {
121
122   /**
123    * Creates an empty {@link Main} element.
124    */
125   public Main() {}
126
127   /**
128    * Creates a {@link Main} element with the specified child nodes.
129    *
130    * @param children The child nodes.
131    */
132   public Main(Object...children) {
133      children(children);
134   }
